body:
@normanmaurer there's another obstacle in supporting this use case where where a cached ByteBuf is sent to multiple clients use SslHandler. I believe that this is a very common and generic use case and it exists in Apache Pulsar. 
The solution idea was to first call `.asReadOnly()` for the original source ByteBuf before adding it to the cache.
However, this won't work since the read-only buffer doesn't support reference counting in the same way as a `.duplicate()` buffer. I've created another issue #14075 about this.
